            <div type="translation">
                <p>The most venerable church of our Lady was erected by the contribution and the great desire of Ioannes Gerakiotes/Moutoullas and his wife Eirene, on the thirtieth of July of the year 6788 (1280).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Partially preserved. The inscription begins with the symbol of a cross. The surname of the founder Ioannes became a subject of much debate between the scholars. Ιt is clear that the surname Gerakiotes was written first and then the surname Moutoullas was added above it. Only the first six letters of the surname Gerakiotes are clearly visible while the others have been overwritten with the last letters of the surname Moutoullas. The words πάνσεπτος, ναός, δεσποίνης, συνδρομῆς, πόθος, καί, συνβίου, Εἰρήνης, μήν, are misspelled. Also, the painter's writing seems to have been influenced by spoken language. This is confirmed by the words [πά]σσεπτος, σηδρομή, τῆ σηνβίου instead of the correct πάνσεπτος, συνδρομῆς, τῆς συμβίας. Accents and breathings with errors.</p>
            </div>
